For authentication and authorization, the suggestion is to use Bearer token as discussed [here](https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/aspnet/core/signalr/authn-and-authz?view=aspnetcore-6.0#bearer-token-authentication).

In our implementation, we did not want to use a bearer token. Instead, we generate a ticket for a specific user with an expiration time.

The client first fetches a ticket from our service. Then, a SignalR connection is established with our service, with the ticket provided under the query parameter “ticket” as shown below:
```
let connection = new signalR.HubConnectionBuilder()
    .withUrl("{endpoint}:{port}/{hubName}?ticket={generatedTicket}")
    .build();
```

On the service, a [hub filter](https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/aspnet/core/signalr/hub-filters?view=aspnetcore-6.0) intercepts and validates the ticket against the connected user:
```
public async ValueTask<object> InvokeMethodAsync(HubInvocationContext invocationContext, Func<HubInvocationContext, ValueTask<object>> next)
{
    var httpCtx = invocationContext.Context.GetHttpContext();
    var ticketId = httpCtx.Request.Query["ticket"].ToString();
    try
    {
        await ValidateTicketAgainstUser(ticketId, invocationContext.Context.UserIdentifier);
    }
    catch (SomeException ex)
    {
        throw new HubException("exception message");
    }
    return await next(invocationContext);
}
```

All this works fine as long as the ticket does not expire. 

In the client code, we want to periodically renew the ticket. Once renewed, we want to update the existing SignalR connection with this newly generated ticket so that subsequent hub method invocations over the _same_ connection starts sending the new ticket.

As mentioned, we have explored the JavaScript client's accessTokenFactory, but this works only if we are sending a bearer token or expecting the hard-coded query parameter "access_token".

Does a callback exist that would let us set the renewed ticket into a custom query parameter, similar to how the value is being set for “access_token”?

